name: compliance-checker
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "5.0.2" %}

package:
  name: compliance-checker
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/c/compliance-checker/compliance-checker-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 5a7924e9bbf13861b250aa1a4719f848f3192c24445f729d441772a2c27b5eb7

build:
  number: 0
  noarch: python
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv
  entry_points:
    - compliance-checker = cchecker:main

requirements:
  host:
    - python >=3.6
    - pip
    - setuptools-scm
  run:
    - python >=3.6
    - cf-units >=2
    - cftime >=1.1.0
    - isodate >=0.5.4
    - jinja2 >=2.7.3
    - lxml >=3.2.1
    - netcdf4 >=1.5.7
    - owslib >=0.8.3
    - pendulum >=1.2.4
    - pygeoif >=0.6
    - pyproj >=2.2.1
    - regex >=2017.07.28
    - requests >=2.2.1
    - setuptools >=15.0
    - shapely >=1.7.1
    - validators >=0.14.2

test:
  source_files:
    - compliance_checker
  requires:
    - pytest
  imports:
    - compliance_checker
    - compliance_checker.cf
  commands:
    - compliance-checker --help

about:
  home: https://github.com/ioos/compliance-checker
  license: Apache-2.0
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: Checks Datasets and SOS endpoints for standards compliance

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - benjwadams
    - daf
    - kwilcox
    - lukecampbell
    - ocefpaf
